      <h1 class='title'>Independent Police Complaints Commission</h1>
    </div>
    <div class='commons-written-statements-sitting' id='content'>
      
      <cite class='section'>HC Deb 01 April 2004 vol 419 cc99-100WS</cite>
      <a class='permalink column-permalink' id='column_99ws' title='Col. 99WS &mdash; HC Deb 01 April 2004 vol 419 c99WS' name='column_99ws' href='#column_99ws' rel='bookmark'>99WS</a>
      <div class='hentry member_contribution' id='S6CV0419P2-00792'>
        <a name='S6CV0419P2_20040401_CWS_3'>  </a>
        <blockquote cite='http://hansard.millbanksystems.com/people/ms-hazel-blears' class='contribution_text entry-content'>
          <a class='speech-permalink permalink' href='#S6CV0419P2_20040401_CWS_3' title='Link to this speech by Ms Hazel Blears' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
          <cite class='member author entry-title'><a href="/people/ms-hazel-blears" title="Ms Hazel Blears">The Minister for Crime Reduction, Policing and Community Safety (Ms Hazel Blears)</a></cite>
          <p class="first-para" id="S6CV0419P2-00792">I am pleased to announce the launch of the Independent Police Complaints Commission, which has now replaced the Police Complaints Authority. It will operate under the<a class='permalink column-permalink' id='column_100ws' title='Col. 100WS &mdash; HC Deb 01 April 2004 vol 419 c100WS' name='column_100ws' href='#column_100ws' rel='bookmark'>100WS</a>
          powers and duties provided to it by the <a href="/acts/police-reform-act-2002">Police Reform Act 2002</a>. Under the Chairmanship of Nick Hardwick, it is responsible for the effective and efficient running of the police complaints system.</p><p id="S6CV0419P2-00793">The IPCC has its headquarters in London, and also has a regional presence in Manchester, Leicester, and Cardiff.</p><p id="S6CV0419P2-00794">As guardian of the complaints system, the IPCC alongside the police service and others will undertake a vital role in maintaining public confidence in the integrity and accountability of the police service.</p>
        </blockquote>
      </div>
